    "problemStatement": "Consider a tree with NNN nodes, rooted at node 111.\n\nThe value of the ithi^{th}ith node (1\u2264i\u2264N)(1 \\leq i \\leq N)(1\u2264i\u2264N) is denoted by AiA_iAi\u200b.\n\nChef defines the function MEX(u,v)MEX(u, v)MEX(u,v) as follows:\n\nLet BBB denote the set of **all** the values of nodes that lie in the **shortest path** from uuu to vvv (including both uuu and vvv). Then, MEX(u,v)MEX(u, v)MEX(u,v) denotes the MEX of the set BBB.\n\nFind the **maximum** value of MEX(1,i)MEX(1, i)MEX(1,i), where 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line of input contains a single integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases. The description of the TTT test cases follows.\nThe first line of each test case contains a single integer NNN - the number of nodes in the tree.\nThe second line of each test case contains NNN space separated integers A1,A2,...,ANA_1, A_2,..., A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,...,AN\u200b. AiA_iAi\u200b represents the value of the ithi^{th}ith node.\nThe following N\u22121N-1N\u22121 lines contain two space-separated integers XXX and YYY, denoting that there exists an edge between the nodes XXX and YYY.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output in a single line, the maximum value of MEX(1,i)MEX(1, i)MEX(1,i) where 1\u2264i\u2264N1 \\leq i \\leq N1\u2264i\u2264N.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641041 \\leq T \\leq 10^41\u2264T\u2264104",
      "1\u2264N\u22641051 \\leq N \\leq 10^51\u2264N\u2264105",
      "0\u2264Ai\u2264N0 \\leq A_i \\leq N0\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264N",
      "1\u2264X,Y\u2264N1 \\leq X, Y \\leq N1\u2264X,Y\u2264N",
      "Sum of NNN over all test cases does not exceed 3\u22c51053 \\cdot 10^53\u22c5105."
    ],
