        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111:\n\nMEX(1,1)=MEX({A1})=MEX({0})=1MEX(1, 1) = MEX(\\{ A_1\\} ) = MEX(\\{ 0\\} ) = 1MEX(1,1)=MEX({A1\u200b})=MEX({0})=1.\nMEX(1,2)=MEX({A1,A2})=MEX({0,1})=2MEX(1, 2) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2\\} ) = MEX(\\{0, 1\\} ) = 2MEX(1,2)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b})=MEX({0,1})=2.\nMEX(1,3)=MEX({A1,A3})=MEX({0,2})=1MEX(1, 3) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_3\\} ) = MEX(\\{0, 2\\} ) = 1MEX(1,3)=MEX({A1\u200b,A3\u200b})=MEX({0,2})=1.\nThus, the answer is 222.\n\nTest case 222:\n\nMEX(1,1)=MEX({A1})=MEX({0})=1MEX(1, 1) = MEX(\\{ A_1\\} ) = MEX(\\{ 0\\} ) = 1MEX(1,1)=MEX({A1\u200b})=MEX({0})=1.\nMEX(1,2)=MEX({A1,A2})=MEX({0,1})=2MEX(1, 2) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2\\} ) = MEX(\\{0, 1\\} ) = 2MEX(1,2)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b})=MEX({0,1})=2.\nMEX(1,3)=MEX({A1,A2,A3})=MEX({0,1,2})=3MEX(1, 3) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2, A_3\\} ) = MEX(\\{0, 1, 2\\} ) = 3MEX(1,3)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b,A3\u200b})=MEX({0,1,2})=3.\nMEX(1,4)=MEX({A1,A4})=MEX({0,3})=1MEX(1, 4) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_4\\} ) = MEX(\\{0, 3\\} ) = 1MEX(1,4)=MEX({A1\u200b,A4\u200b})=MEX({0,3})=1.\nThus, the answer is 333.\n\nTest case 333:\n\nMEX(1,1)=MEX({A1})=MEX({1})=0MEX(1, 1) = MEX(\\{ A_1\\} ) = MEX(\\{ 1\\} ) = 0MEX(1,1)=MEX({A1\u200b})=MEX({1})=0.\nMEX(1,2)=MEX({A1,A2})=MEX({1,2})=0MEX(1, 2) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2\\} ) = MEX(\\{1, 2\\} ) = 0MEX(1,2)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b})=MEX({1,2})=0.\nMEX(1,3)=MEX({A1,A2,A3})=MEX({1,2,3})=0MEX(1, 3) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2, A_3\\} ) = MEX(\\{1, 2, 3\\} ) = 0MEX(1,3)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b,A3\u200b})=MEX({1,2,3})=0.\nMEX(1,4)=MEX({A1,A2,A4})=MEX({1,2,4})=0MEX(1, 4) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_2, A_4\\} ) = MEX(\\{1, 2, 4\\} ) = 0MEX(1,4)=MEX({A1\u200b,A2\u200b,A4\u200b})=MEX({1,2,4})=0.\nMEX(1,5)=MEX({A1,A5})=MEX({1,0})=2MEX(1, 5) = MEX(\\{ A_1, A_5\\} ) = MEX(\\{1, 0\\} ) = 2MEX(1,5)=MEX({A1\u200b,A5\u200b})=MEX({1,0})=2.\nThus, the answer is 222."
